Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hey Kimonjol,  Unfortunately, Swappy network did not meet its softcap, and thus, Swappy network had to cancel the sale and refund all contributions. Our reputation is our most important asset. We are going to do the right thing by our community, who believed in us and in our dream. So, expect to be refunded in your Blockhaus¬¥ TGEApp profile within 7 days after the end of the ICO (May 26th). We were very unfortunate with the timing of launch. But the beauty of being an entrepreneur is that failure = learning. You can always try again, and with the added benefit of being older and wiser. We still believe in the power of the Blockchain to change the world, and we will keep working to make it happen. Thank you for believing on us and in our dream."

Author: lps21
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hi everyone,  I was reading the whitepaper and came across one of the reasons why we need universal credit that Swapy can provide:  A signi cant reason why two billion individuals lack access to nancial services is because traditional banks can not find cost-effective means of servicing all populations, especially those at the bottom of the socio-economic pyramid. This could be attributable to the prohibitive distances that potential customers must travel to bank branches, or because such populations do not earn enough money for the banks to value them as clients. The consequence is that these individuals are excluded from the global credit ecosystem.  This is an excerpt from the whitepaper of Swapy, page 7. For more on the whitepaper, please click on this link: https://bit.ly/2qhddHM

Author: Felicisimoiii
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: I invite everyone who haven't read this one yet    Answering Due Diligence Questions Written by Edmilson Rodrigues (CEO at Swapy Network)   Every once in a while we receive a list of due diligence questions. It is very useful to share the answers with the whole community, because it can help to solve other people‚Äôs doubts.  Q1: As part of your use case, Swapy Network will be the facilitator between the investor and the credit company. Do you have a list of credit companies/entities that you have already talked with who are willing to participate in your network? A: We have been working close with 3 credit companies from Brazil to validate their needs while building our tool. We can not disclose their names because they are not officially our clients yet, but there is a great interest among the new digital lenders to join our network, as we can reduce their cost of funding in half.  Q2: How will Swapy network credit-score the loan applicant? Will this credit scoring be done by swapy or a 3rd party? A: We adopted an Open Innovation approach. So, Swapy Network will be the way to aggregate and share people¬¥s financial data, but the actual credit scoring for each loan will be done either by the Credit companies lending to the applicants, or by a especialized credit scoring company. We are in advanced talks with one of the biggest Alternative Credit Scoring companies in the world to join the Swapy Network and offer their model for the companies, charging for it in Swapy Tokens.  You can read the rest of the article here: https://medium.com/swapynetwork/answering-due-diligence-questions-8f5d79402f49

Author: lps21
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hey everyone,  Just wanted to share what how Swapy plans to solve problems of access to credit:  1. It facilitates offers of credit in order to lower the costs of capital. 2. It eliminates information asymmetry between participants through a commonly shared and updated data network. 3. It provides better data so that credit companies can make better lending decisions and offer lower rates to good clients. 4. It encourages lower cost capital and better information which can reduce entrance barriers for new companies.  If you want to read more about Swapy, the whitepaper is located on this link: https://bit.ly/2qhddHM

Author: kieran_84
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: That's right meaamir86, Swapy believe they can achieve ‚ÄúUniversal Access to Credit‚Äù through three applications.  The first is the Swapy Exchange, which aims to connect smart money to emerging economies. It will introduce international investors from countries where the interest rates are comparatively low to credit companies in countries where the interest rates are comparatively high, providing better returns to the investors and lower cost capital for the credit companies.  The second is Swapy Financial ID, which aims to empower people, giving them a financial identity that has the purpose to be valid anywhere in the world.  And the third is Swapy Data Market, which aims to transform users' nancial data into self-determined value through a token-based system. This suite of decentralized applications will allow the individuals to hold their own data and to choose how many tokens they receive in exchange for it, and when, and with whom they want to share.  Together these three applications tackle several issues which have made ‚ÄúUniversal Access to Credit‚Äù not yet possible.

Author: Felicisimoiii
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hello Community Members,  We are proud to share with you this article,  The challenges of designing for blockchain: How I designed Swapy Exchange UX  "The main challenge when designing for a new technology that can certainly revolutionize the world as we know it, but that has not already reached its boom, as blockchain, is to humanize the technology, to make it user-friendly, and it is not an easy task. Translate the technical view, gathering engineering decisions into feasible interfaces can be tricky. The strategy we defined was to start simple and improve continuously, providing the necessary features to run the platform with satisfactory user experience, and constantly improve it based on our real user‚Äôs feedback."  Link: https://medium.com/swapynetwork/the-challenges-of-designing-for-blockchain-how-i-designed-swapy-exchange-ux-537e33c27340

Author: VasilyVIP
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: What's the main difference between Swapy and other P2P lending services?

Author: tulio
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hi Vasily, we are starting with a different approach than the P2P solutions. With our first DApp (available in alpha: https://www.swapy.network) we will allow already established credit providers from emerging nations (high interest rates) to have access to capital from investors from developed nations (low interest rates) with no intermediaries, and then provide more affordable loans to underserved people contributing to financial inclusion - everything traceable, thanks to blockchain technology. This is a faster go to market strategy since they already have the distribution channels and operations established, and are also compliant with countries' regulation.   We also solve the problem of information asymmetry with two other proposed DApps: a self-sovereign identity and a p2p data market place powered by this decentralized identities. We expect that in the medium term, we will have the infrastructure (on top of Ethereum blockchain) to perform tasks such as financial data storage and processing in a decentralized manner (homomorphic encryption and data mining may help to keep the privacy). It would be a second layer network of nodes receiving rewards in SWAPY.  So, I would argue that the main difference is that we cover the pillars of the problem (high spread in emerging nations and lack of good information about the borrowers) in a whole and we are up to build something that is much more than just smart contracts, but also the needed infrastructure to accomplish our mission of Universal Access to Credit.

Author: luksbit
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: And what would be the soft cap? Will KYC data validation be requested? Will these discounts reported on the website be for pre-sale only? Will I have access to the private keys of my assets in the plataform?

Author: tulio
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hi liksbit, thanks for your questions! See the answers below:  1) Softcap: $5 million USD 2) KYC is mandatory 3) There will be discounts for presale and crowdsale. Also, our presale is open to any whitelisted member with no min cap. Please check it here: https://goo.gl/1fER7t  --- If with "platform" you mean "Blockhaus Token Sale app" just read below: 4) If you mean during the ICO, we outsourced the sales to our partners at Blockhaus, a highly experienced team in token sales. Their sales app uses metamask as wallet, you will have full control of your assets.  --- If with "platform" you mean "Swapy Network" just read below:   4) Regarding Swapy platform, decentralization is our key focus. You will have full control of your data and private keys. This is why we are using Metamask as DApp wallet (both browser and desktop). Recently we made a huge effort to integrate Metamask with desktop versions as well in the best way we could achieve (better than some other integrations). Check this post out: https://medium.com/swapynetwork/integrating-metamask-with-electron-a-simple-secure-and-non-intrusive-approach-517a04da1656

Body: Hi tulio, thanks you for the clarification. I have registered the download of the app and will wait for further updates. With regards to the signature campaign, a few questions if you could help  1. Is 21 articles required every week or total by end of the campaign? If the latter, when is the current planned end date for the campaign? 2. For qualified relevant article, does it have to contain web links? Does the article also need to be about the swapy project? Author: tulio
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hi rainbow196,  Thanks for your questions. See my answer followed by our bounty rules' quotes:  1) You must create at least 21 relevant post during the whole campaign. It is not every week.  "Write at least 21 relevant posts during the campaign period, and you will be eligible for the bounty and receive the rewards after Swapy Network Team evaluations;"  2) It depends.  a) If we are talking about relevant posts for BitcoinTalk, you will already have your signature attached to the post, so it is enough. It is important to be concise with the topic because we do not want our bounty participants to flood BitcoinTalk (and any other media) with spams. The key idea here is to inform and engage people with our goals.  "NOTE: We will consider that posts are relevant if they: (1) Provide complete and reliable information in regard to the original posts; (2) They create interactive dialogue and discussions, but they need to be cohesive and consistent; (3) Posts must contains links with interesting and reliable sources; (4) Interesting images and videos are welcome as a compliment for the posts."  b) If we are talking about social media or blogging (Twitter, Facebook, Medium, etc), you must provide at least one link to any Swapy's official content (website, blog, bitcointalk, etc).  "When the tweet is created by yourself, it must contains links from us, such as official website and our username on Twitter @SwapyNetwork"  "Contents must be unique and set up to public view, not private. The content must contain official links of Official Swapy Network Website or social media; (facebook, Twitter)"   --> Regarding our D'app download, you should have received an email with the link to download (Mac, Windows, Linux). This week we will be releasing our browser app integrated to Metamask extension. This will allow those on Chrome OS and other operating systems to test our D'Apps.  Let me know if it helps!

Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit

However, I triggered your email a few minutes ago so you can provide your feedback earlier on. We appreciate your sincere comments since it will provide us with rich information to keep improving! Thanks!!

He told this story in this recent post. We have the pleasure to tell you that, in addition to being an early investor, Tim Draper will join our current pre-ICO round and be an advisor to Swapy Network.  We are very grateful to Tim Draper. Not only for creating Draper University, the place which educated hundreds of entrepreneurs and empowered them to pursuit their dreams and solve the problems they are most passionate about. But also for all his support and evangelism for the blockchain technology in general. He famously predicted that Bitcoin would reach $10,000 in 2018. Which gave him the nickname of the Nostradamus of the Market. For those who do not know Tim Draper personally, he is a great mentor and business partner. His name is a beacon of trust to the world. He is always kind and available. Always knows how to encourage the entrepreneurs and advise them to think big, be bold and aim to change the world. Ed, our CEO, was emotioned to receive this kind reference from Tim to a prospective investor in our company:  Want to get to know Tim Draper, the RiskMaster, personally? Apply for Draper University: http://www.draperuniversity.com/ Are you an accredited investor? Email our CEO at ed@swapy.network .

Author: tianyi321
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: there are many concern efficient credit project these days, i know it's a highly profitable business, but i cann't possibly put my money into each project. so tell me Why should I invest in this? what is make your project different than others? Which is your project core competition?

Author: swpceo1
Title: [ANN][ICO] Swapy Network: The Solution for Universal Access to Credit
Body: Hi Tianyi321 . Thanks for your question. I am the CEO of Swapy Network, and it is a pleasure to talk.  Here are some key differences between us and the other projects:  1) The founders are from Brazil. In our country, the average loan has a 145% interest rate. We lived the problem of high cost of credit in our own skin. That is why we are so passionate to solve it and we will never give up on it.  2) We are obsessed with compliance and before proposing our solution, we consulted legal experts in three countries: Brazil, USA and Switzerland. Therefore, many other projects that depend on a pure P2P model will not work in Brazil, for example, because the legislation does not allow it.  3) We have world class investors and advisors. We have Tim Draper as our early investor and Don Tapscott as our advisor,  4) Our project is already in public Alpha. You can try it here: https://www.swapy.network/download  5) We are the one stop shop for a cheaper credit, and we work with the existing infrastructure. While some other ICO projects work providing the capital for the loans, and other work providing a credit scoring, Swapy Network is a complete solution for both problems.  6) We are Open Source. Which means that other teams from around the world can join our project and get paid to develop or improve it. We took this decision because we believe that we are #StrongerTogether!  If you have any doubt, please let us know.
